    <p><em>Last updated: April 2025</em></p>

    <h2>1. Data Controller</h2>
    <p>The data controller for personal data collected through this website is the operator of <strong>It's A Malamute</strong> (itsamalamute.netlify.app), reachable at: <strong>hello@itsalamute.com</strong></p>

    <h2>2. Types of data processed</h2>

    <h3>Navigation data</h3>
    <p>The computer systems and software procedures used to operate this website acquire, in the course of their normal operation, certain personal data whose transmission is implicit in the use of Internet communication protocols. This data includes IP addresses, browser type, operating system, domain name of the connecting computer, URI addresses of requested resources, and request timestamps. This data is used solely to obtain anonymous statistical information on site usage and to verify correct functioning.</p>

    <h3>Data voluntarily provided by the user</h3>
    <p>Sending an email to the addresses listed on this website involves the acquisition of the sender's email address and any other personal data included in the message. Data provided by email is used exclusively to respond to the request and is not shared with third parties.</p>

    <h2>3. Cookies and tracking technologies</h2>
    <p>For detailed information about the cookies used by this site, please see our <a href="/en/cookie-policy/">Cookie Policy</a>.</p>

    <h2>4. Third-party services</h2>

    <h3>Netlify (hosting)</h3>
    <p>This site is hosted by Netlify, Inc. (San Francisco, USA). Netlify processes access data for the purpose of providing the hosting service. Netlify privacy policy: <a href="https://www.netlify.com/privacy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">netlify.com/privacy</a></p>

    <h3>Google Analytics (if consent provided)</h3>
    <p>With the user's consent, this site uses Google Analytics, a web analytics service provided by Google LLC (USA). Google Analytics uses cookies to collect anonymous data about site usage. IP addresses are anonymised before transmission to Google. Google LLC participates in the EU-US Data Privacy Framework. Google privacy policy: <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">policies.google.com/privacy</a>. Users may withdraw consent at any time via the link at the bottom of this page.</p>

    <h2>5. Legal basis for processing</h2>
    <p>Navigation data is processed on the basis of the controller's legitimate interest (Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR) to ensure the technical functioning of the site. Processing via analytics cookies occurs exclusively with the user's prior consent (Art. 6(1)(a) GDPR).</p>

    <h2>6. Retention periods</h2>
    <p>Navigation data is not retained beyond the time strictly necessary for service provision. Data transmitted by email is retained for the time needed to handle the request. Data collected via Google Analytics (if consent given) is retained for 14 months, per Google Analytics 4 default settings.</p>

    <h2>7. User rights</h2>
    <p>With respect to personal data processed, users have the right to: access their data (Art. 15 GDPR); request rectification (Art. 16) or erasure (Art. 17); request restriction of processing (Art. 18); object to processing (Art. 21); withdraw consent at any time without affecting the lawfulness of prior processing; lodge a complaint with the supervisory authority (in Italy: Garante per la protezione dei dati personali – <a href="https://www.garanteprivacy.it" target="_blank" rel="noopener">garanteprivacy.it</a>).</p>
    <p>To exercise your rights, write to: <strong>hello@itsalamute.com</strong></p>

    <h2>8. International transfers</h2>
    <p>Some third-party services listed (Netlify, Google) involve the transfer of data to the United States. Such transfers are carried out in compliance with GDPR safeguards, in particular through participation in the EU-US Data Privacy Framework or the adoption of Standard Contractual Clauses approved by the European Commission.</p>

    <h2>9. Changes to this policy</h2>
    <p>We reserve the right to make changes to this privacy policy at any time. Changes will be indicated by updating the date at the top of the page.</p>

